      "author": "kriss-spy",
      "description": "## What's New\n\n### WebSocket Editor Server (#4)\n- Auto-discovers vault as an OpenCode editor via lock file\n- JSON-RPC handshake with initialize / notifications/initialized\n- Sends at_mentioned messages on file drop\n- Lazy start/stop tied to terminal view lifecycle\n\n### Drag and Drop Improvements (#1, #2, #3)\n- Single internal note drops via dragManager\n- External OS file drops via dataTransfer.files fallback\n- Multi-file drops with staggered delivery\n- Vault-relative path normalization\n- No PTY keystroke injection — pure WebSocket protocol\n\n### Technical\n- Added ws dependency for WebSocket server\n- 16 tests passing\n- Production build verified in Electron Node.js context",
      "downloadCount": 2,
